org.purl.co.interfaces
Interface COBag<E>

All Superinterfaces:
COCollection<E>, java.util.Collection<E>, java.lang.Iterable<E>
All Known Subinterfaces:
COList<E>
All Known Implementing Classes:
StandardCOBag, StandardCOList
public interface COBag<E>
extends COCollection<E>

This interface represents a CO bag, i.e., a CO collection without order but with repetition.

Author:
Paolo Ciccarese, Silvio Peroni

add

boolean add(java.net.URI coitemuri,
            E o)
This method adds a new object to the bag, that will be dereferenced through a new CO item created starting from the URI specified as input.

Parameters:
coitemuri - the URI of the item dereferencing the object of the bag.
o - the object to add.
Returns:
true if the object it is correctly added, false otherwise - i.e., coitemuri exists within the bag.

remove

boolean remove(COItem<E> item)
This method removes from the bag the CO item indicated and, consequently, decreases by 1 the number of objects o contained by the bag.

Parameters:
item - the CO item to be removed.
Returns:
true if the item has been removed, false otherwise.
